org.jcvi.jillion.experimental.trace.archive2

Class TraceArchiveWriter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jcvi.jillion.experimental.trace.archive2.TraceArchiveWriter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public final class TraceArchiveWriter
extends Object
implements Closeable
    TraceArchiveWriter is a class that can write out a complete Trace Archive folder structure which contains the following files:
    • TRACEINFO.XML
    • README
    • fasta folder: contains 1 fasta file per record
    • pos folder: contains 1 position fasta file per record
    • qual folder: contains 1 quality fasta file per record
    • traces folder: contains 1 binary trace per record
    Author:
    dkatzel

      TraceArchiveRecordDataException is a checked Exception that is to be thrown when an error occurs while creating metadata for a TraceArchiveRecord.

      • TraceArchiveWriter

        public TraceArchiveWriter(File rootDir,
                          Map<TraceInfoField,String> commonFields,
                          TraceArchiveWriter.TraceArchiveRecordCallback recordCallback,
                          String volumeName,
                          Date volumeDate,
                          String volumeVersion)
                   throws IOException
        Create a new TraceArchiveWriter.
        Parameters:
        rootDir - the root directory of where to write out the trace archive; if this parameter is null, then the current directory is used (not recommended). If the given directory does not exist, then it will be created.
        commonFields - Map of common fields that should be included in all trace archive records; if no common fields should be used, then include and empty collection, can not be null.
        recordCallback - an instance of TraceArchiveWriter.TraceArchiveRecordCallback can not be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the root directory given does not exist, and an error occurs trying to create it.
        NullPointerException - if recordCallback, commonFields is null or if any key or value in commonFields is null.
